For your SECOND vaccine:
Your appointment for your second dose will be 21 days later at the same location as your first dose (this may be written on the back of your white vaccination card).
•	You may have received an email confirming the place and date of your second dose appointment - please confirm the time of the appointment.
•	If you did not receive an email, please go to the location where you got your first dose at the same time as your first appointment. Remember to bring your white vaccine record card or electronic vaccine record AND a photo ID. Please check your spam folder.
•	We strongly encourage you to keep your appointment. In a rare instance where you must reschedule (for instance if you have an emergency) please contact Public Health on the email address that will be provided.

Scheduling instructions for your SECOND VACCINE (from the County website):

•	Your appointment for your second dose will be 28 days later at the same location or closest as your first dose (this may be written on the back of your white vaccination card).
•	You may have received an email confirming the place and date of your second dose appointment - please confirm the time of the appointment.
•	If you did not receive an email, please go to the location where you got your first dose at the same time as your first appointment. Remember to bring your white vaccine record card or electronic vaccine record AND a photo ID. Please check your spam folder.
•	We strongly encourage you to keep your appointment. In a rare instance where you must reschedule (for instance if you have an emergency) please contact Public Health on the email address that will be provided.
